article.headline: Indiana St. 59, Illinois St. 24
article.story: TERRE HAUTE, Ind. -- Ronnie Fouch threw four touchdown passes, Bryant Kent had 118 yards receiving and two scores and Indiana State defeated Illinois State 59-24 Saturday. Fouch was 16 of 22 for 250 yards, Kent had seven receptions and Shakir Bell added 146 rushing yards and one TD for the Sycamores (3-2, 1-1 Missouri Valley). Matt Brown had three touchdown passes for the Redbirds (3-3, 2-2), and Tyrone Walker caught five passes for 131 yards and two scores. Darrius Gates added two rushing TDs for Indiana State, which compiled 579 total yards and has scored at least 50 points in each of its wins this season. The Sycamores scored on nine of their 12 possessions, including their first seven, and pulled away with 30 points in the second quarter.
